                <head>437. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 10, 1970, Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_DS1">Suleyman
                        Demirel</persName> postponed his visit to the United States, citing among
                    other reasons his desire to be in Ankara when the Turkish Parliament voted on an
                    opium licensing bill.</p>
            </div>
